AJGMCFNDKEG: Kamisato Ayaka's outfit. This kimono features an armor-coated skirt, displaying the nobility and resilience of the Shirasagi Himegimi.
Ayaka's travel outfit. Its design is based on the Fontaine dresses depicted in light novel illustrations and seems to serve as a window into the lifestyle of proper ladies who live in that nation.
Jean's outfit. Neat and smart clothing that emphasizes her chivalry.
Jean's summer wear. Light and cool, but no less elegant for it. The perfect choice for a trip to the seaside.
Jean's outfit. This classic knight's ceremonial outfit is suited to all manner of occasions.
The Traveler's outfit. A practical set of clothing to wear during a long journey.
Lisa's outfit. A slim-fit dress adorned with roses that displays a young lady's elegance.
An outfit Lisa had someone commission for her when she revisited Sumeru. A perfect blend of practicality and elegance, the dress bears a resemblance to Lisa's old uniform from her Akademiya days.
The Traveler's outfit. A practical set of clothing to wear during a long journey.
Barbara's outfit. A Deaconess's uniform from the Church of Favonius with a unique Barbara streak running through it.
Barbara's beach attire. This pretty skirt brims with summer vitality and carries with it a cool ocean breeze.
Kaeya's outfit. Fashionable clothes festooned with a fur collar.

Kaeya's outfit from his role as the "Dagger Bandit" in the play. Though flamboyant and designed to be as eye-catching as possible, it isn't difficult to put on, though it does take some time to get all the accessories and daggers sorted.
Diluc's outfit. A smart and tasteful suit fit for a nobleman.

One of the outfits Diluc wears during covert actions, it resembles a flame dancing in the shadows. The crimson red traces it leaves behind at the edges of the enemy's vision will scar their nightmares forever.
Razor's outfit. Rough and ready clothes suited for running out in the wilderness.
Amber's outfit. An Outrider's uniform made for maximum mobility.
Amber's outfit. This is a more formal — but no less cool — version of the Outrider's uniform!
Venti's outfit. The clothes of a carefree bard.
Xiangling's outfit. Light and comfortable clothing brimming with fiery passion.
Beidou's outfit. Lightweight clothing saturated with a brave seafarer's spirit.
Xingqiu's outfit. Fine robes woven from the high-quality silk sold by the Feiyun Commerce Guild.
Xiao's outfit. Classical battle-wear fit for a thousand years of evil-conquering.
Ningguang's outfit. Intricate embroidery is the hallmark of this graceful dress.
Ningguang's formal wear. The long cyan skirt traces her elegant curves, and the butterfly wings at her ankles lend the outfit a touch of light grace.
Klee's outfit. A set of clothing for an energetic child that even comes with a matching leather backpack.

An exquisite outfit Klee wears only for the most important performances. The colors are brilliant, like a cake adorned with cream flowers and crowned with scarlet candles. With it comes happiness and smiles that will fill your adventures.
Zhongli's outfit. This is the leisurewear of choice for Zhongli, the Wangsheng Funeral Parlor's consultant.
Fischl's outfit. The Prinzessin der Verurteilung's customary vestments during her sojourn upon this realm.
A ceremonial outfit for the Prinzessin. May she who is noble retain her courage, sincerity, and kindness forever, such that no evil shall ever overcome her.
Bennett's outfit. An old adventurer's uniform that has been patched and sewn up in various places.
Tartaglia's outfit. Illustrious attire that signifies Childe's position as the eleventh Fatui Harbinger.
Noelle's outfit. Heavy clothing made of durable velvet and metal plates.
Qiqi's outfit. A herb gatherer's garment that brings her great peace of mind due to the attached talismans.
Chongyun's outfit. A traditional thaumaturge's trappings.
Ganyu's outfit. Elegant clothes blessed by the mighty and illuminated adepti.
Albedo's outfit. The Knights of Favonius alchemist's uniform that Albedo often wears when conducting his experiments.
Diona's outfit. The work uniform of the Cat's Tail's star bartender.
Mona's outfit. A light astrologist's outfit that does away with superfluous fabric to provide top quality at an affordable price.
Mona's outfit. A costume made specifically to encompass the astrological concept of "the destined moment," thanks to the 30% discount ticket she got from the celestial globe refund.
Keqing's outfit. A formidable-looking dress made using luxurious materials.
Keqing's formal wear. Amidst the beautiful dawn of the Lantern Rite, the threads weaved by days of hard work intertwine into a light yet magnificent appearance.
Sucrose's outfit. A Knights of Favonius alchemist's uniform customized for Sucrose.
Xinyan's outfit. A rocker's stage costume adorned with spikes.
Rosaria's outfit. Rosaria has heavily modified this particular Church of Favonius uniform.
Rosaria's outfit. This seems to have been custom-made for her by the Church.
Hu Tao's outfit. The daily work clothes of the Wangsheng Funeral Parlor's director.
Kaedehara Kazuha's outfit. The maple leaf patterns are the hallmark of this wandering samurai's clothes.
Yanfei's outfit. The dress that the legal adviser Yanfei wears when she heads out to visit clients.
Yoimiya's outfit. A patchwork of memories from festivals over the years.
Thoma's outfit. He cropped the pieces of this light suit of armor till only the thigh and arm guards were left, allowing him to comfortably attend to all matters in and out of combat.
Eula's outfit. Consummate elegance shines through in this neat and smart knight's uniform.
The Raiden Shogun's outfit. This kimono has been adorned with the Electro Mitsudomoe, granting it the highest honor in the land.
Sayu's outfit. Marvelous attire designed after the mysterious animal known as the Mujina.
Sangonomiya Kokomi's outfit. A noble's dress decorated with little precious objects produced in Watatsumi Island.
Gorou's outfit. This light armor is designed to allow the marksman-general Gorou to handle his bow with ease. The armoring at the shoulder and elbow is also designed with this in mind.
Kujou Sara's outfit. Prim and proper, it is a garment worthy of an Archon's devout servant.

Itto's outfit. It has an uncommon air of awesomeness about it, and the oni mask worn at the hip is quite imposing indeed — certainly enough to reduce even the naughtiest child of Hanamizaka to terrified tears.

Yae Miko's outfit. A shrine maiden uniform that declares her lofty position as the Guuji of the Grand Narukami Shrine to all. May the lovely sight of her in that dress remain forever, just as the Sacred Sakura emblazoned upon her pure white skirt, which will never wilt away.
Shikanoin Heizou's outfit. Having taken his outer coat off and tucked it around his waist, the Tenryou Commission detective cuts quite the dashing figure.
Yelan's outfit. It has lurked alongside its wearer in the shadows over many a year, to the point where the outfit almost has a mysterious temper of its own, like an orchid blooming at midnight.
Kirara's outfit. The famous designer Chiori followed the principle of "comfortably wearing a beautiful flower upon one's body" when creating this outfit for Kirara.
Aloy's outfit. A hunter's garb suited to life in the wilds.
Shenhe's outfit. These elegant garments have accompanied her through long years of training. The red ropes that surround her body are fetters and wards simultaneously.
Yun Jin's outfit. It was made by skilled tailors from the Feiyun Commerce Guild. Yun Jin fell in love with it at first sight, and it is now her favorite set of casual wear.
Kuki Shinobu's outfit. The iconic oni mask she wears symbolizes her role as the Arataki Gang's terrifying "demonic deputy."
Kamisato Ayato's outfit. The kimono itself is made using uncommon fabrics, and its patterning recalls a mountain spring, giving off a feeling of calm and stability that matches its wearer.
Collei's outfit. Now that she no longer needs to remain bundled in a thick cloak, she is free to emerge like a newly-sprouted leaf and welcome every lovely sunrise.

Dori's outfit. This outfit almost begs to be further adorned with gems and precious metals, loudly announcing its wearer's love of wealth to the world. And they say that this is the merchant Dori's casual wear... So does this mean that she has clothes even more expensive than this one!?
Tighnari's outfit. Clad in the colors of wood, tree, and flower, Tighnari is surrounded at all times by natural life, determined even in fashion sense to put the "forest" in "Forest Watcher."
Nilou's outfit. It is neither flower nor mist, but when she begins to dance, both seem to bloom into being.

Cyno's outfit. This garb displays the General Mahamatra's dignity and the just principles he sticks by. It was a rather complicated piece to commission due to Cyno's request for the custom-made head ornaments and requires regular maintenance.
Candace's outfit. No matter where she goes, the golden sands and the nights of her homeland that adorn her clothes go together with her.
Nahida's outfit. Only the oracles that interpret knowledge may robe the God of Wisdom, and so even the smallest ornament is viewed by believers as holy writ.
Layla's outfit. In the depths of quiet nights, the stars that dot the sky wrap her like a cloak, guiding her into sweet dreams — well, or so she dearly wishes might happen.
Wanderer's outfit. An ascetic's garb and hat can provide the wanderer some shelter from the rain, but they can do nothing to quell the winds and storms raging within.
Faruzan's outfit. The relatively plain yet elegant style represents her unfaltering purity. This style was very popular in the Akademiya a hundred years ago, but has now become an uncommon sight.

Yaoyao's outfit. A lovely, short jacket Yaoyao's parents made for her. As the little girl travels safely between Qingce Village and Liyue Harbor, this jacket, along with the adeptal bells her master gave her, always keeps her company.
Alhaitham's outfit. "Don't bother the Scribe with trivialities... What do you think those soundproofers of his are for, anyway?"\nSo observed an experienced staff member at the Temple of Silence.

PMPMKOPBJHA: The Lioness and the Blazing Sun
AJGMCFNDKEG: Dehya's outfit. It is said when the lion roars, even the scorching sun will quiver. Though Dehya is long past the age of believing in such stories, it doesn't stop her from gazing upon the sun sinking below the sands, reminiscing about the tales and storytellers of her childhood.

Mika's outfit. This knightly outfit, specially designed for field work, is made using a vast multitude of flexible but tough materials, adding plenty of places for the wearer to store his weapons and tools. Dressed and prepared, fortune is certain to stride alongside the wearer of this outfit with each step into the unknown.

Kaveh's outfit. A notable tailor from Treasures Street created these clothes in imitation of the lovely sight of birds extending their wings in flight and would only sell them to those who knew how to appreciate their beauty.
Baizhu's outfit. The cloak on his shoulder is dyed using Changsheng's favorite plants. Its fragrance lingers and soothes the senses.
Lynette's outfit. A cat resides in the shadows until it wishes to show itself — inscrutable, just like a magician's assistant.
Lyney's outfit. Cats only stretch in front of those they trust completely. Otherwise, they merely hide their claws behind a smile — intimate yet reserved, just like the sweet words of this magician.
Freminet's outfit. This suit wraps around the deep diver like a second skin, his constant companion in countless sallies to the silent seabed.
Wriothesley's outfit. It radiates both dignity and strength, with the rugged gray wolf chain serving as the mark of his rulership over the Fortress of Meropide.

Neuvillette's outfit. The solemn, elegant garb of the Iudex. The complexity in its design does, in fact, cause some inconveniences in movement, but to its wearer, that it matches his standing is a more important matter.
